Pennsylvania’s Republican gubernatorial nominee Doug Mastriano believes the violent attack on the U.S. Capitol on Jan. 6, 2021, “distant” and “detached from reality.” Appearing on conservative talk radio station News Talk 103.7 FM on August 10, Mastriano also denounced the House Select Committee’s investigation into the Jan. 6 insurrection and discussed his brief virtual appearance before the committee, explaining why he decided to cut the interview short.&nbsp;



