Mastriano, who has been identified by the Jan. 6 committee as a key figure in the insurrection, was being interviewed about his own role in the planning and execution of the attack. Mastriano was spotted marching outside of the Capitol on the day of the insurrection and even breached police barricade lines, according to video footage obtained by the committee. In addition to supporting and repeating former President Donald Trump’s election lies, Mastriano spent thousands of dollars on transportation to help shuttle Trump supporters from Pennsylvania to Washington, D.C., on the day in question and was in regular communication with the former president at the time.&nbsp;




